      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PACIFIC EAGLE (3) was out of the money two runs back at Gloucester Park then displayed pleasing improvement last start to score by 4 metres over 2190m at Bridgetown. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets a similar line up so he is capable of getting the job done again. THE DARK NIGHT (6) broke in the run and finished fourth, beaten 9 metres, first-up last time out over 1780m at Northam. This doesn't look as hard so he can bounce back. BATAVIA WEST (7) is on the radar after her last-start sixth over 1177m at Pinjarra six days ago. ALTA HURRAH NZ (5) finished tenth two runs ago then broke and finished a distant eighth over 2223m at Narrogin at the latest appearance. Won't find this any harder and he can bounce back to top-three form.",
